  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2025-08-05",
    "date": "2026-03-31T19:15:58Z",
    "text": "This bill prohibits a state where the congressional districts have been redistricted after a decennial census from carrying out another redistricting until after the next apportionment of Representatives following a decennial census, unless a court requires the state to conduct a subsequent redistricting to comply with the Constitution or enforce the Voting Rights Act of 1965.\n\nThe bill is applicable to any congressional redistricting which occurs after the November 2024 election."
  },
